OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F412A1772697873
OL,3,CAnne Boleyn's 'extraordinary' chair on
OL,4,Cdisplay for first time at childhood
OL,5,Chome
OL,7,FA chair that experts believe was made
OL,8,Fespecially for Henry VIII's wife Anne
OL,9,FBoleyn is on display at Hever Castle
OL,10,Ffor the first time.
OL,12,FThe chair is being shown at her
OL,13,Fchildhood home as part of an
OL,14,Fexhibition called Capturing a Queen:
OL,15,FThe Image of Anne Boleyn.
OL,17,FIt's thought that the chair was made
OL,18,Fbetween 1510 and 1520, long before
OL,19,FAnne became Queen of England upon
OL,20,Fmarrying Henry VIII in 1533.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G1/7
